Tests:

1. Create user without including all fields:
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:13000/register/ -d '{"username": "janedoe", "password": "2020flex"}' -H "Content-Type: application/json"


2. Get user authorization token for a non existing user:
curl -X POST -d '{"username": "randomusername","password": "randompassword"}' -H 'Content-Type: application/json'  http://127.0.0.1:13000/api-token-auth/


3. Login user without including token:
curl -X GET http://127.0.0.1:13000/api-auth/login/'


4. List all users as non admin:
curl -X GET http://127.0.0.1:13000/users/ -H 'Authorization: Token some user token'


5. Open account as non admin:
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:13000/accounts/ -d '{"holder": 45, "account_type": "Credit", "balance": -1000}' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -H 'Authorization: Token d934874c3ca9be2d3105c7d08762d8dfc0a31c88'

6. List account for a non existing user id, using admin access:
curl -X GET http://127.0.0.1:13000/accounts/?user_id=45 -H 'Authorization: Token d934874c3ca9be2d3105c7d08762d8dfc0a31c88'


7. Withdraw all money from Savings account:
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:13000/transactions/ -d '{"account": 8, "transaction_type": "Withdrawal", "amount": 2000000}' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -H 'Authorization: Token 5fbbd05f74991a739dad591f6bf6ad737d651365'
Note: Choose account with balance less than the withdrawal amount

8. View Transactions using admin access:
curl -X GET http://127.0.0.1:13000/transactions/ -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -H 'Authorization: Token 5fbbd05f74991a739dad591f6bf6ad737d651365'
